Features
    Panels
        Control
            Use grid to hide Gcode row if height is too small
            G-Code Parser
                UI setting
            G-Code Parameters
                UI setting
            Auto Complete
        Jogging
            Set default feed rate max($110, $111, $112)
            Limit Jogging to work area fetched from $$
        Stream
            TBD
        Settings
            SetDisable based on state / reset
            Settings
                $$ - View Grbl settings
                $x=val - Save Grbl setting
                    $0 – Step pulse, microseconds
                    $1 - Step idle delay, milliseconds
                    $2 – Step port invert, mask
                    $3 – Direction port invert, mask
                    $4 - Step enable invert, boolean
                    $5 -  Limit pins invert, boolean
                    $6 -  Probe pin invert, boolean
                    $10 - Status report, mask
                    $11 - Junction deviation, mm
                    $12 – Arc tolerance, mm
                    $13 - Report inches, boolean
                    $20 - Soft limits, boolean
                    $21 - Hard limits, boolean
                    $22 - Homing cycle, boolean
                    $23 - Homing dir invert, mask
                    $24 - Homing feed, mm/min
                    $25 - Homing seek, mm/min
                    $26 - Homing debounce, milliseconds
                    $27 - Homing pull-off, mm
                    $30 - Max spindle speed, RPM
                    $31 - Min spindle speed, RPM
                    $32 - Laser mode, boolean
                    $100 – X steps/mm
                    $101 – Y steps/mm
                    $102 – Z steps/mm
                    $110 – X Max rate, mm/min
                    $111 – Y Max rate, mm/min
                    $112 – Z Max rate, mm/min
                    $120 – X Acceleration, mm/sec^2
                    $121 – Y Acceleration, mm/sec^2
                    $122 – Z Acceleration, mm/sec^2
                    $130 – X Max travel, mm
                    $131 – Y Max travel, mm
                    $132 – Z Max travel, mm
            Startup Lines
                $N (Print startup lines)
                $Nn=<gcode> (Store startup line, where n is the line number)
            Build Info
                View build info ($I)
                    [VER:v1.1f.20170131:Some string]
                    [OPT:VL,16,128]
                Set id string ($I=xxx)
            Restore Defaults
                $RST=$ (Restore Defaults: Settings ($$)
                $RST=# (Restore Defaults: G-Code Parameters ($#))
                $RST=* (Restore Defaults: All ($$, $#, $N, $I))
            Save / Restore
        Script
            TBD
            Tool changing
                Intercept M6
                Run macro, eg:
                    Pause the machine (!).
                    Move the spindle to a user-defined "Tool Change Position" (e.g., front of the machine).
                    Wait for you to physically swap the bit.
                    Run a Probe Cycle to measure the new tool length (critical step).
                    Update the Z-zero height to match the new tool length.
                https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-2jFvlvu0co&t=1s
        Buttons
            Per-axis homing (build option)
            Custom Programs
                ie: probe, go to Predefined Position etc
    Misc
        Scrolling
            Only scroll to end if view position is already at the end
                if not, change color to indicate there's new text
        TCP serial port server from https://github.com/fornellas/serialtcp
        Keyboard navigation (tab / btab / arrows etc)
        Codebase
            Add internal/
            Add line limits to various TextView
